{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/00006-week-3-100-days-of-flutter/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"erluxman","author":"Laxman Bhattarai"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e0dc0c57-58d8-57f8-9f6b-5c304e68da25","html":"<h2 id=\"day15-flexible-vs-expanded\"><a href=\"#day15-flexible-vs-expanded\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day15 Flexible vs Expanded</h2>\n<p>Expandable() is nothing more than Flexible() with </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Flexible (fit: FlexFit.tight) = Expanded()</code></pre></div>\n<p>whereas Flexible uses fit as FlexFit.loose by default. </p>\n<p>If you are confused with what tight and loose mean, tight means it wants to fit tightly with it’s parent where loose means it wants to be as loose as possible. </p>\n<p>That’s why, no matter how much flex you give to default Flexible, it won’t take any more space than just enough for it’s child to fit in it. But it also doesn’t allow it’s Sibling widgets to take that space it couln’t take.</p>\n<p>Whereas  Expanded by default takes as much of the space it can take that is allocated by flex(flex means how much of the space it can take from parent).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://codepen.io/erluxman/pen/JjYKZGG\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">try in codepen</a></p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/54b03a8dc5ed8697082882e65daa9e01/9eaa0/15expandedvs